  <bulletin id="4" date="20160324">
    <sections>
      <section>
        <title>Japan Real Estate</title>
        <chapter>
          <title>Before</title>
          <subtitle>Causes</subtitle>
          <paragraph>There are more worker, better labour conditions and office vacancies. Lower mortgage taxes bring more house purchasing and house starts with higher residential land prices. New economic policies and a weaker yen bring more inbound visitors and investments. Demand for hotels and more tourism make stronger the retail sector and higher commercial land value.
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <chapter>
          <title>After</title>
          <subtitle>Consequences</subtitle>
          <paragraph>The nationwide land price  increased from 2015 (0,9%). Pace gains in commercial land price with an annual acceleration of 2,9%. real estate sector is moving and new buildings are rising.
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <keywords>
          <keyword name="Southeastern Asia"/>
          <keyword name="Investments"/>
          <keyword name="Housing Real estate"/>
        </keywords>
        <sources>
